ice which afterwards gave the margraves of brandenburg the rights of prince elector once he was firmly established in the northern march albert covetous eye lay also on the thinly populated lands to the north and east for three years he was occupied in campaigns against the slavic wends who as pagans were considered fair game and whose subjugation to christianity was the aim of the wendish crusade of in which albert took part albert was part of the army that besieged demmin and at the end of the war recovered havelberg which had been lost since diplomatic measures were more successful and by an arrangement made with the last of the wendish princes of brandenburg pribislav of the hevelli albert secured this district when the prince died in taking the title margrave in brandenburg he pressed the crusade against the wends extended the area of his mark encouraged german migration established bishoprics under his protection and so became the founder of the margraviate of brandenburg in which his heirs the house of ascania held until the line died out in in feud with henry son henry the lion duke of saxony was interrupted by pilgrimage to the holy land on his return in he with the consent of his sons siegfried not being mentioned donated land to the knights of saint john in memory of his wife sofia at werben at the elbe in albert accompanied emperor frederick barbarossa to italy where he distinguished himself at the storming of milan in albert joined league of princes formed against henry the lion and peace being made in albert divided his territories among his six sons he died on november possibly in stendal and was buried at ballenstedt cognomen foundation of the memorial to albert at spandau citadel albert personal qualities won for him the cognomen of the bear not from his looks or qualities for he was tall handsome man but from the cognisance on his shield an able man had quick eye as well as strong hand and could pick what way was straightest among crooked things wa